Trim the @salad leaves{120%g} and roughly chop.

Chop the @tomato{1} into 1cm chunks.

Drain the @sweetcorn{1%pack} in a #sieve{}.

Just before serving, toss the salad leaves with @honey mustard dressing{1%sachet}.

Place a #pan{} over medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}.

Add the @diced Irish chicken breast{260%g} and season with @Mexican style spice mix{2%sachets}, @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Fry until golden brown and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to packaging we use to keep it fresh.

Divide the salad between #plates{} and top with Mexican-spiced chicken.

Spoon the corn and diced tomato over the top.